[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Exploring Snappy Loader Options**\n\nI'm thinking about not relying on reflection. Maybe I could launch a Java process to utilize an external JVM that isn't captured by the native-image agent, though that seems unlikely to be helpful. \n\nI might create a temporary file before loading Snappy with the exact filename to reach a specific line of code. To prepopulate it, I'd need to look into copying a resource. I'd also want to ensure that calls from the test count correctly in this context.\n\n**Analyzing Class Loading Issues**\n\nI can't have both in one class due to the static `isLoaded` variable. However, for dynamic-access coverage, I might manage by having one file with multiple tests, even though execution order can be uncertain. It seems I need a single process since static loading can't be repeated. \n\nI wonder if using a `forkEvery` option in tests could help, but that's unlikely. I might explore calling `SnappyLoader.findNativeLibrary`, but that’s package-private and disallowed for reflection. Using the public API on a child seems tricky too.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0b01435cdb5be1c0016a3d6a20f558819381e51680460b3d02\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqPWo0azJ32eeYey95GnIMqbdsakCDq7L6Jh6Ss34zVXdZUDdKFTJIkN71CRbRH9N7uO3WO0THvggam-suJYGkErBYhzkujkqlN2TbemingjkUI3L9wezBe3GHPuKWmOBNZWu9s5NupXO2VKJrYvgOlURfuGDAFsvSHGHXY1EjgYosz030D-z1VCmbtWOThM3GaUGcmv6zyQ_KJrJf04us55_utnzD7bFPmHJSOqbdlZo4qkW-98-Q0yWT_jL-G4moHG8yYwLeak6IYb_PsCu4hSPSG6pAzx4IuFzTT-Ars4GhcgeqFVmgMafufnC-P6sQLH4kxFnhdEiZog0OC6_YgZaacQMGW7fnH9gsESBbqY493x-xzAkX2vo5QAtJzFXS8xWMwiCnwyZdRc_LpRD6J0f-Qf8Wqvd2LS8nwRXIqe-acc6NxqcwPkzp7bjP3O-AdwBzwlEcg9sXj4gAPidYhK8HcDQpJO6U05Cqd82XBOnDmBQXxNiHkK3IQYsEspMDdMdhcHGN6WS6AMCGKZiCg8-oClJbAwUCvZaBky_6Eih62bCMYdeGzayyLlgmfqEC0YFMhx6SYb5qg8VJx1sUlyOtNkPjSm1_ujxzRKdxbyBmxaZ07F3REJejmGoVp5zQEQjFQ_8_hNui0Gd5oe8Xxef